The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, March 7: Chemicals and fertilisers minister Ram Vilas Paswan today said farmers would continue to get fertilisers at the minimum retail price fixed by the government. The minister said public funds provided by way of subsidy to make fertilisers available to farmers at affordable prices cannot be wasted. 

 New Delhi, March 7: GoAir today said it would fly to three more cities, taking the total number of destinations covered to 14, by April. The airline will also add five more aircraft by the year-end. 

 Calcutta, March 7: The Birlas? counsel today claimed before Calcutta High Court that under the law governing succession, if Priyamvada Birla had inherited the property from her husband M.P. Birla, on her death and being childless, it would devolve upon the heirs of her husband. 

 New Delhi, March 7: Bharti Enterprises today said it expected to start its life insurance venture with Axa of France by June-end. Last week, the FIPB has cleared Axa?s proposal to infuse Rs 24.55 crore for its 26 per cent stake in the joint venture. 

 New Delhi, March 7: Sebi has constituted a committee to study the future of regional stock exchanges after demutualisation.




